9 An Act relating to students; amending Section 1,
Chapter 297, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section
10 6-401), which relates to electronic or digital
communications between students and school personnel;
11 providing for inclusion of alternate adult in
communications with certain students; providing
12 exception; updating statutory reference; providing an
effective date; and declaring an emergency.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 1, Chapter 297, O.S.L.
17 2024 (70 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section 6-401), is amended to read as
18 follows:
19 Section 6-401. A. As used in this section:
20 1. “Electronic or digital communication” includes, but is not
21 limited to, emails, text messages, instant messages, direct
22 messages, social media messages, messages sent through software
23 applications, and any other electronic digital means of
24 communication; and
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB799 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 2. “School personnel” means teachers, coaches, administrators,
2 school bus drivers, or any other persons employed full-time or part-
3 time by a public school or charter school.
4 B. 1. School personnel engaging in electronic or digital
5 communication with an individual student shall include the student’s
6 parent or, guardian, or alternate adult provided for in paragraph 2
7 of this subsection in any electronic or digital communication,
8 unless such communication is on a school-approved platform and
9 related to school and academic communications.
10 2. Students who are known to be homeless children and youth as
11 defined in Section 600 of Title 10 of the Oklahoma Statutes shall,
12 in lieu of a parent or guardian, have an alternate adult included in
13 the electronic or digital communication. The alternate adult shall
14 be:
15 a. the McKinney-Vento homeless liaison of a public
16 school, or
17 b. a case manager or designated employee of a homeless
18 shelter, transitional living program, or a continuum
19 of care lead agency.
20 C. Exceptions to the requirement in subsection B of this
21 section may be made in case of an emergency, subject to subsequent
22 notification to the parent or, guardian, or alternate adult provided
23 for in paragraph 2 of subsection B of this section. The provisions
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB799 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 of s ubsection B of this section shall not apply to the alternate
2 adult provided for in paragraph 2 of subsection B of this section.
3 D. School personnel shall make reasonable efforts to use
4 school-approved platforms, systems, or applications that allow
5 automatic inclusion of parents or, guardians, or alternate adults
6 provided for in paragraph 2 of subsection B of this section in
7 communications with students.
8 D. E. Schools shall provide training, developed by the State
9 Department of Education, for school personnel on the student
10 communication requirements of this section.
11 E. F. Any school personnel who is reported to be in violation
12 of subsection B of this section shall be put on administrative leave
13 while the school district investigates the incident and notifies the
14 board of education. If the investigation finds that no misconduct
15 occurred, the school personnel shall be reinstated and the incident
16 shall be noted in the school personnel’s employee file. If the
17 investigation finds misconduct occurred, the school personnel shall
18 be disciplined according to the school district board of education’s
19 policy, up to and including termination of employment, and the
20 incident shall be reported to law enforcement pursuant to Section
21 1210.163 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes this title.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
23 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB799 SFLR Page 3
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 decl ared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
2 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
3 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON EDUCATION
